 EPIC 1: User Authentication
 Backend Stories
1.1 — [BACKEND] User Model & DB Setup

Define User table with Prisma (id, username, email, hashed password).

Configure and run migrations.

Add validation constraints.

1.2 — [BACKEND] Register API

POST /api/auth/register (username, email, password).

Validate input, hash password, store in DB.

Return success or validation error.

1.3 — [BACKEND] Login API

POST /api/auth/login (email, password).

Verify credentials, return JWT token.

Handle failure cases cleanly.

1.4 — [BACKEND] JWT Middleware

Implement middleware to protect future routes.

Create /api/auth/profile to test token verification.

 Frontend Stories
1.5 — [FRONTEND] Login Page UI

Build index.html with login/register modal using JS and HTML/CSS.

Include validation and toggle modal logic.

1.6 — [FRONTEND] Register/Login Integration

Send credentials to backend API.

Store JWT token in localStorage.

1.7 — [FRONTEND] Auth Session Check

On page load, verify JWT and redirect user to /feed.html if authenticated.
